      "body" : ">macOS makes encrypting USB drives nearly trivial (stores password in keychain), not sure about other OS's.\r\n\r\nBitLocker is not available for \"Home\" SKUs of Windows.\r\n\r\nEFS requires the drive to be formatted into NTFS, and, EFS is well known for its backfires - countless users had lost access to their EFS-encrypted files because they didn't notice the importance of backuping the private key.",
